value.name: ‘A long time coming’: Through a pandemic, the Naval Academy Class of 2021 celebrates in-person graduation with family
value.description: Approximately 275 Marine Corps second lieutenants and 786 Navy ensigns commissioned Friday after attending the Naval Academy. Families gathered in the stands of the Navy-Marine Corps Stadium, something that loved ones were unable to do for last year’s academy graduation because of the coronavirus pandemic.
